## 🧹 **How to Permanently Delete All Claude AI Chats in Bulk (Works Only on PC – Not Android/iPhone Yet!)**

If you’re looking to start fresh or wipe all your Claude.ai conversations in one go, this guide will show you exactly how to **bulk delete every chat** at once—step by step.

> ⚠️ **Important:** As of June 2025, **bulk deletion is only available on Windows, macOS, and Linux via a desktop browser**. You **cannot delete multiple chats at once on Android or iPhone**—you’d have to delete each one manually, one by one.

---

### ✅ **METHOD 1: Manual Bulk Deletion via Claude's Website**

1. **Open Claude in your browser**
   → Go to: [https://claude.ai/recents](https://claude.ai/recents)

2. **Enter Selection Mode**

   * Click the **“Select”** button in the top-right corner.

3. **Select All Chats**

   * Once in selection mode, click **“Select All”** to highlight every conversation.

4. **Delete All**

   * Click the red **“Delete Selected”** button and confirm.

🎉 That’s it—**your entire Claude chat history is now permanently deleted.**

---

### ⚡ **METHOD 2: One-Click Wipe Using a Browser Extension (Advanced Users)**

If you want to delete everything even faster, use a browser extension:

1. **Install the Chrome extension: `Claude Chat Cleaner`**

   * Search in Chrome Web Store or go to a trusted GitHub repo if available.

2. **Open Claude.ai**

   * Make sure you're signed in to your account.

3. **Click the extension icon → “Clear Chats”**

   * It will automatically loop through your chat list and remove them all.

🛑 **Warning:** This extension performs irreversible bulk deletion. No undo.

---

### ❌ NOT POSSIBLE ON MOBILE (YET)

* **Android/iPhone Limitations:**

  * The Claude app or mobile browser doesn’t support multi-select or “Select All.”
  * You must manually delete chats one at a time by opening them and choosing "Delete."

---

### 🧠 Pro Tip:

Before deleting, consider **copying or exporting any important chats** you want to save. Claude does **not** offer chat exports natively—so you’ll need to manually copy text into a document.

